President Donald J. Trump spoke with President Muhammadu Buhari of Nigeria to discuss the cooperation between the United States and Nigeria in areas such as security, economy, and governance. Trump expressed the importance of the relationship between the two countries and expressed interest in expanding the partnership. They agreed to continue working together in the fight against terrorism, and Trump expressed support for the sale of aircraft to assist Nigeria in its fight against Boko Haram. Trump also thanked Buhari for his leadership in the region and emphasized the importance of a strong and prosperous Nigeria.